        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>August 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#160;&#160;<placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName> <placeName>164 Ludlow Street</placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>August 25&#44; 1853</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
			<p>Very honored friend&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">You are the noble man who first drew the attention<lb/> and aroused the community of our land in the condition of the Jews of<lb/> <placeName>China</placeName>. All the communities from <placeName>East</placeName> to <placeName>West</placeName> have therefore expressed<lb/> the wish that as your agent I should occupy myself also with this<lb/> thing. They have therefore commissioned me to travel to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> and have a committee organized by you in which you should act as pre&#45;<lb/>sident. When I Passed through <placeName>Albany</placeName>&#44; <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> <sic>madea</sic> suggestion&#44; that<lb/> it would be to the best interests of the cause if you were to choose<lb/> <placeName>New York</placeName> as the organization point for this committee. He&#44; too&#44; wants<lb/> to contribute his share to this holy cause&#44; and by word of mouth pre&#45;<lb/>sent his completely formulated plans. On the <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> of this month&#44; at<lb/> 6 o&#39;clock in the morning&#44; he will arrive here and will wait for you <sic>t</sic><lb/> till <date>Monday</date> evening. I therefore beg of you&#44; upon the receipt of this<lb/> letter&#44; to let me know whether you will come or not. If you intend to<lb/> come&#44; let me know beforehand where you intend to lodge&#44; and bring along<lb/> for me 6 prayer books of the Ashkenazic ritual and 2 sets of pentateuchs<lb/> all bound. If you do not want to come&#44; I shall go to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> next<lb/> week and take these things along with me. Whether <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> will make<lb/> the journey to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> or not&#44; the other members of this community&#44;<lb/> whom you are to name&#44; will not make the journey. That <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> will<lb/> deny revelation in his work&#44; is a lie on the part of <add>&#63;</add>......&#8212;a<lb/> brazen lie. On the contrary&#44; everything is as it should be.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Your eternal friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>164 Ludlow St.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="On other side">It is self&#45;understood that the cost of the trip will be returned to you&#44;<lb/> and that only the &#8220;Occident&#8221; will be the organ in which the progress of<lb/> this thing will be revealed to the public.</p>
		<pb n="Envelope"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
